  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to send prepare a transaction so that I can send a transaction.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Improvement\r\n\r\nThe send transaction screen is at the heart of every Ethereum transaction and core to Status so we need users can seamlessly send transactions.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nAt a glance users can understand the transaction detail and sign.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nUsers get confused about the recipient, account balances, amounts, etc.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"216\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-04-27 at 2 47 40 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/116099/39363261-f4f4c64c-4a29-11e8-9eca-1f7faabfa135.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n\r\n- Clearly shows what the transaction is for. Eg person, dapp, etc.\r\n- Shows Fiat cost\r\n- Shows crypto cost\r\n- Shows fees\r\n- Emphasize final price\r\n- Offer escape route\r\n- Shows balance\r\n- Removes \"sign later\"\r\n\r\nAlso let's explore adding a confirmation screen\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional\r\n\r\nUXR insight:\r\n<img width=\"876\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-04-13 at 3 29 06 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/116099/39363024-07cf768c-4a29-11e8-844e-adb3b8850699.png\">\r\n<img width=\"804\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-04-13 at 3 30 29 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/116099/39363038-18e25c8c-4a29-11e8-82ff-363811b028e9.png\">\r\n",
